The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Kanpur, Sept. 24 (PTI): A teenager sleeping in his car with its AC on suffocated to death yesterday.          Vinay Gupta, 18, had gone to sleep in the car, parked inside his garage, after a power cut at his home. This morning, his family found him dead with smoke coming out of the vehicle.                  
	 Calcutta: The Bengal government has sanctioned Rs 10 crore to pay a festival grant of Rs 2,000 each to bus, minibus, taxi and autorickshaw employees who became jobless after the phasing out of vehicles older than 15 years. The grant, however, covers only employees of vehicle owners who have applied for replacement by August 25.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The office of the leader of Opposition in the Lok Sabha comes under the purview of the transparency act, the Central Information Commission has said. The observation came at a hearing of a petition seeking information from L.K. Advani his letter to the Prime Minister on black money in Swiss banks.                   
	 Thiruvananthapuram: Kerala CPM secretary Pinarayi Vijayan, accused in the Lavalin scam, has filed a plea saying A.K. Antony, chief minister when the deal with the Canadian firm was initiated, be probed.
                                                                                                                           
